Where ∆N(t) is the number of events in the time interval [t, ∆t), H(t) is the history of the event process at time t. Since event counts (i.e. Poisson process) modelling approach assumes that the events are independent such that the event history process at t, H(t), does not affect the instantaneous probability of an event at time t, the intensity function is reduced to the rate function ρ(t) below;M2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
